WITH 
  -- Filter customers with the least amount of consumption paid in CZK for 2013
  min_consumption_customers AS (
    SELECT 
      Segment, 
      CustomerID, 
      SUM(Consumption) AS total_consumption
    FROM 
      yearmonth
    JOIN 
      customers ON yearmonth.CustomerID = customers.CustomerID
    WHERE 
      Currency = 'CZK' AND 
      Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY 
      Segment, 
      CustomerID
    ORDER BY 
      total_consumption
  ),
  
  -- Calculate annual average consumption for each segment
  avg_consumption_per_segment AS (
    SELECT 
      Segment, 
      AVG(total_consumption) AS avg_annual_consumption
    FROM 
      min_consumption_customers
    GROUP BY 
      Segment
  )

-- Calculate differences in annual average consumption between segments
SELECT 
  'SME vs LAM' AS segment_pair, 
  (SME.avg_annual_consumption - LAM.avg_annual_consumption) AS difference
FROM 
  avg_consumption_per_segment SME
CROSS JOIN 
  avg_consumption_per_segment LAM
WHERE 
  SME.Segment = 'SME' AND 
  LAM.Segment = 'LAM'

UNION ALL

SELECT 
  'LAM vs KAM' AS segment_pair, 
  (LAM.avg_annual_consumption - KAM.avg_annual_consumption) AS difference
FROM 
  avg_consumption_per_segment LAM
CROSS JOIN 
  avg_consumption_per_segment KAM
WHERE 
  LAM.Segment = 'LAM' AND 
  KAM.Segment = 'KAM'

UNION ALL

SELECT 
  'KAM vs SME' AS segment_pair, 
  (KAM.avg_annual_consumption - SME.avg_annual_consumption) AS difference
FROM 
  avg_consumption_per_segment KAM
CROSS JOIN 
  avg_consumption_per_segment SME
WHERE 
  KAM.Segment = 'KAM' AND 
  SME.Segment = 'SME';	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing

WITH consumption_eur AS (
  SELECT 
    ym.CustomerID, 
    ym.Date, 
    ym.Consumption, 
    c.Segment
  FROM 
    yearmonth ym
  JOIN 
    customers c ON ym.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
  WHERE 
    ym.Date BETWEEN '201201' AND '201312' 
    AND c.Currency = 'EUR'
),
increases AS (
  SELECT 
    Segment, 
    SUM(CASE WHEN Date LIKE '2012%' THEN -Consumption ELSE Consumption END) AS increase,
    SUM(CASE WHEN Date LIKE '2013%' THEN Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS total_2013
  FROM 
    consumption_eur
  GROUP BY 
    Segment
)
SELECT 
  Segment, 
  (increase / total_2013) * 100 AS percentage_increase
FROM 
  increases
ORDER BY 
  percentage_increase DESC;	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
